To ensure the category is saved to your Google Sheet and displayed correctly in the app, the **Google Apps Script** on your Google Sheet must be updated to handle the 4th column. 

The frontend is sending the `category` data, but your current script (provided in the first message) only processes 3 columns (`date`, `amount`, `name`). When the app refreshes, it sees the missing data from the sheet and defaults to "Uncategorized".

### 1. Update your Google Apps Script
Please replace the functions in your Google Sheets Script Editor with this version:

```javascript
function doGet(e) {
  const sheetName = e.parameter.sheet || "Transcations";
  const ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet();
  const ws = ss.getSheetByName(sheetName);
  const data = ws.getDataRange().getValues();
  const headers = data.shift();

  const json = data.map(row => ({
    date: row[0] instanceof Date ? row[0].toISOString().split('T')[0] : row[0],
    amount: row[1],
    name: row[2],
    category: row[3] || "" // This reads the 4th column
  }));

  return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify(json))
    .setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
}

function doPost(e) {
  const params = JSON.parse(e.postData.contents);
  const ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet();
  const ws = ss.getSheetByName(params.sheet || "Transcations");

  // Append 4 columns: Date, Amount, Name, Category
  ws.appendRow([
    params.date,
    params.amount,
    params.name,
    params.category || "" 
  ]);

  return ContentService.createTextOutput("Success")
    .setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.TEXT);
}
```

### 2. Frontend Updates
I am making the `TransactionForm` more robust to ensure the category is never sent as `undefined` and updating the fetching logic to correctly extract single-column data from your "Category" sheet.

